result.name: Tsui Wah Restaurant

reviews.text: I had several meals here because of its convenient location. While other restaurants had a line up on Friday night, there was none here. Still quite busy but service is quick. I most enjoyed their breakfast set and fish ball noodles. Their Hainanese chicken set was good except for the rice which was too garlicky. The baked pork chop rice was terrible-bland and fatty pieces of pork. It’s best to stick with the recommendations on the menu and to observe what the locals are ordering.

Quite nice tasty dish however it’s not the dish that I ordered. Had similar ingredients to the one that I would of got, just had a few extra prawns for a few dollars. Also the milk tea, there were two types but the waitress still put down the wrong one. Same as the standard tea that is served in Hong Kong (tea with condensed milk, not cow’s milk from carton)
The food is bad for my taste. The service is ok. The cleanliness is not what I expect from HK standard.
Large area for seating and good sized tables, extensive menu, large serving sizes and reasonable prices. Milk tea is worth a mention.
Very good food for price
